        <div class="translation-block animate-in">
          <div class="translation-code">
            <span class="translation-label">CODE · Python (simplified agentic loop)</span>
<pre><code><span class="code-line">message = client.messages.<span class="code-function">create</span>(</span>
<span class="code-line">    model=MODEL_NAME,</span>
<span class="code-line">    messages=[{<span class="code-string">"role"</span>: <span class="code-string">"user"</span>, <span class="code-string">"content"</span>: user_message}],</span>
<span class="code-line">    tools=tools,</span>
<span class="code-line">)</span>
<span class="code-line"></span>
<span class="code-line"><span class="code-keyword">if</span> message.stop_reason == <span class="code-string">"tool_use"</span>:</span>
<span class="code-line">    tool_use = <span class="code-function">next</span>(b <span class="code-keyword">for</span> b <span class="code-keyword">in</span> message.content <span class="code-keyword">if</span> b.type == <span class="code-string">"tool_use"</span>)</span>
<span class="code-line">    tool_result = <span class="code-function">process_tool_call</span>(tool_use.name, tool_use.input)</span>
<span class="code-line"></span>
<span class="code-line">    response = client.messages.<span class="code-function">create</span>(</span>
<span class="code-line">        model=MODEL_NAME,</span>
<span class="code-line">        messages=[</span>
<span class="code-line">            {<span class="code-string">"role"</span>: <span class="code-string">"user"</span>, <span class="code-string">"content"</span>: user_message},</span>
<span class="code-line">            {<span class="code-string">"role"</span>: <span class="code-string">"assistant"</span>, <span class="code-string">"content"</span>: message.content},</span>
<span class="code-line">            {<span class="code-string">"role"</span>: <span class="code-string">"user"</span>, <span class="code-string">"content"</span>: [{</span>
<span class="code-line">                <span class="code-string">"type"</span>: <span class="code-string">"tool_result"</span>,</span>
<span class="code-line">                <span class="code-string">"tool_use_id"</span>: tool_use.id,</span>
<span class="code-line">                <span class="code-string">"content"</span>: tool_result,</span>
<span class="code-line">            }],</span>
<span class="code-line">        }],</span>
<span class="code-line">        tools=tools,</span>
<span class="code-line">    )</span></code></pre>
          </div>
          <div class="translation-english">
            <span class="translation-label">Line-by-Line Explanation</span>
            <div class="translation-lines">
              <p class="tl"><strong>Lines 1-5:</strong> First call to Claude, passing along the "tool specification list."</p>
              <p class="tl"><strong>Line 7:</strong> Claude didn't answer directly -- <code>stop_reason == "tool_use"</code> means it wants to use a tool. It pauses and waits for you to execute.</p>
              <p class="tl"><strong>Line 8:</strong> Extract "the tool-use block" from Claude's response -- get the tool name and parameters.</p>
              <p class="tl"><strong>Line 9 (the real work):</strong> Your program executes using the tool name and parameters Claude provided -- and gets the result.</p>
              <p class="tl"><strong>Lines 11-22 (critical):</strong> Second call to Claude -- insert the tool result back into the conversation history using the special <code>tool_result</code> role. This step is key -- you must preserve the full conversation context so Claude knows "the result from the tool I asked for has come back."</p>
              <p class="tl"><strong>In real scenarios this process may loop multiple times -- until stop_reason != "tool_use", the loop isn't done.</strong></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Screen 4: Spot the bug -->
      <section class="screen animate-in">
        <h2 class="screen-heading">Spot the Bug: Find the Wrong Line</h2>
        <p>Below is an <em>incorrect</em> agentic loop. Claude called a tool but the agent never gives a final response -- find the critical bug line:</p>

        <div class="bug-challenge">
          <div class="bug-code">
            <div class="bug-line" data-line="1" onclick="checkBugLine(this, false)">
              <span class="line-num">1</span>
              <code>message = client.messages.create(model=MODEL, messages=msgs, tools=tools)</code>
            </div>
            <div class="bug-line" data-line="2" onclick="checkBugLine(this, false)">
              <span class="line-num">2</span>
              <code>if message.stop_reason == "tool_use":</code>
            </div>
            <div class="bug-line" data-line="3" onclick="checkBugLine(this, false)">
              <span class="line-num">3</span>
              <code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;tool_use = next(b for b in message.content if b.type == "tool_use")</code>
            </div>
            <div class="bug-line" data-line="4" onclick="checkBugLine(this, false)">
              <span class="line-num">4</span>
              <code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;tool_result = process_tool_call(tool_use.name, tool_use.input)</code>
            </div>
            <div class="bug-line bug-target" data-line="5" onclick="checkBugLine(this, true)">
              <span class="line-num">5</span>
              <code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;print(tool_result)&nbsp;&nbsp;# Got the result, just print it and we're done</code>
            </div>
            <div class="bug-line" data-line="6" onclick="checkBugLine(this, false)">
              <span class="line-num">6</span>
              <code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;return tool_result</code>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bug-feedback" id="bug-feedback"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="callout callout-warning" style="margin-top: var(--space-8)">
          <div class="callout-icon">🐛</div>
          <div class="callout-content">
            <strong class="callout-title">This is the most common root cause of bugs when vibe coders use Cursor / Claude Code</strong>
            <p>"I told the AI to call a tool, it seems to have called it, but the final response still doesn't use the tool's result" -- 99% of the time it's this bug: missing the second <code>messages.create</code> that feeds the <code>tool_result</code> back to Claude. <strong>Printing the tool result is not the answer -- you must insert the result back into the conversation history and call Claude again to get a final response.</strong></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

